\f2 ) \'96 Fragrance, aroma, breath.\
	\'95	Physical Root: Scent, vapor, wafting in the air.\
	\'95	Theological Echo: Spiritual allurement; the first awakening of faith.\
\
The Fragrance Wave in Song of Songs:\
	\'95	1:3: \'93Your name is like purified oil poured forth.\'94\
	\'95	2:13: \'93The vines are in blossom; they give forth fragrance.\'94\
	\'95	4:16: \'93Let my beloved come to his garden and eat its choicest fruits.\'94\
\
The Wave of Fragrance:\
	\'95	Faith is awakened as fragrance draws the soul closer.\
	\'95	Fragrance precedes contact, like the Word proclaimed before full understanding.\
	\'95	It beckons but does not yet bind.\
\
Contrast with Pagan Idolatry:\
	\'95	Pagan use of incense focuses on manipulation of the divine, while biblical fragrance reveals presence and trust.\
\
