\
The Flame Wave in Song of Songs:\
	\'95	8:6: \'93Set me as a seal upon your heart\'85 for love is as strong as death, its flame is the flame of Yahweh.\'94\
\
The Wave of the Flame:\
	\'95	Love consumes as intimacy reaches full covenantal union.\
	\'95	This fire cannot be quenched\'97it is divine, unstoppable, eternal.\
	\'95	It is the symbol of marriage, sacrifice, and worship.\
\
Contrast with Pagan Idolatry:\
	\'95	Pagan fire rituals sought manipulation of power.\
	\'95	The flame of Yahweh is self-giving and transformative, not destructive.\
\
V. Triadic Harmony in the Garden-Wave\
\
The Song of Songs reveals a progressive triad that mirrors faith, hope, and love:\
\
Phase	Symbol	Physical Root	Spiritual Meaning	NT Reflection\
Fragrance (Faith)	Aroma	Air, Breath	Awakening to God\'92s Presence	The Word Proclaimed (John 1)\
Garden (Hope)	Enclosure	Walled, Cultivated	Covenant Intimacy and Trust	The Church (Eph. 5:25-27)\
Flame (Love)	Fire	Consuming Heat	Divine Union and Transformation	The Cross (Rev. 19:7-8)\
\
VI. Christ as the Fulfillment of the Garden-Wave\
\
The Garden-Wave points forward to Jesus Christ:\
	\'95	Fragrance: Christ as the sweet aroma of sacrifice (2 Cor. 2:14-16).\
	\'95	Garden: Christ as the new Adam restoring Eden (John 20:15).\
	\'95	Flame: Christ as the consuming fire of love and sacrifice (Heb. 12:29).\
\
VII. Practical Application of the Garden-Wave Framework\
	1.	In Worship:\
	\'95	Fragrance: Let Scripture proclamation draw the soul in.\
	\'95	Garden: Create covenantal spaces of trust and faithfulness.\
	\'95	Flame: Seek worship as consuming devotion, not entertainment.\
	2.	In Relationships:\
	\'95	Fragrance: Let relationships start with trust and respect.\
	\'95	Garden: Build covenantal boundaries that protect.\
	\'95	Flame: Celebrate lifelong commitment as a sacramental union.\
	3.	In Personal Growth:\
	\'95	Fragrance: Pursue knowledge that awakens the spirit.\
	\'95	Garden: Cultivate spiritual disciplines.\
	\'95	Flame: Seek the transforming fire of God\'92s Spirit.\
\
VIII. Conclusion: From Fragrance to Flame, Union with God\
\
The Song of Songs\'92 Garden-Wave reveals more than romance\'97it reveals spiritual progression from desire to covenant to consuming union. It is a prophetic framework leading the soul from the first call of faith into the full flame of divine presence.\
